All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioPanel
    AudioPanel is the entity that displays the volume controls at the bottom of the screen.
    Bark
    The object representing the players bark "attack".
    Bone
    The Bone class is the entity needed to be collected in order to progress to the next level.
    BoneListener
    BoneListener is the object responsible for managing collisions with Bone objects.
    BreakablePlatform
    BreakablePlatform template for creating obstacles that can be removed with a bark.
    CollisionHandler
    CollisionHandler is the object responsible for managing most of the collisions between objects.
    Controller
    The controller object takes keyboard inputs and outputs interprets them as actions that the player character can take.
    ControlPanel
    ControlPanel is the entity that displays the control bar and health of the player at the top of the screen.
    Game
    Main runnable class of the program.
    GameLevel
    GameLevel is the template for the level classes.
    LevelDebug  
    LevelOne  
    LevelThree  
    LevelTwo  
    MyView
    MyView is an entity used to display images in the background and foreground.
    NullLevel  
    Platform
    The Platform entity is one that the player can stand on.
    Player
    The Player object is the main entity in the game, and the one used by the player in the game
    PlayerScore
    PlayerScore is an entity used to display the players score without having it constantly updating every frame.
    SaveReader
    SaveReader reads save files and returns a player to the start of their chosen level.
    SaveWriter
    Save writer writes level data to a file.
    Spike
    The Spike class is an object that when collided with causes damage.
    TennisBall
    The tennis ball is an object that when collided with increases score.
    Tracker
    Tracker is an entity used to follow the movements of a body in the x-axis.
